You could cast the type to common protocol `CustomStringConvertible`, the `description` property returns the string representation:

    let value = hit?[&quot;im_code&quot;] as? CustomStringConvertible ?? &quot;&quot;
    cell.textLabel?.text = value.description

You got a few options here:

    let value = yourDict?[&quot;im_code&quot;] // Assuming Any? as the type

**The Good**

    if let value = value as? String {
    	cell.textLabel?.text = value
    } else if let value = value as? Int {
    	cell.textLabel?.text = String(value)
    }

**The Bad**

    if let value = value {
    	cell.textLabel?.text = &quot;\(value)&quot;
    }

**The Ugly**

    let text: Any = (value as? String) ?? (value as? Int) ?? &quot;&quot;
    cell.textLabel?.text = &quot;\(text)&quot;

